    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "My one serious piece of advice having used Fable a bunch before release is that, unless you are careful it develops its own internal bizarre cadence &amp; dialogue over long tasks. If you aren't asking it report in plain language, this starts to creep into everything, including menus",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2072543365124481045",
    "time": "2026-07-02 12:50",
    "created_at": "Thu Jul 02 04:50:18 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2072543365124481045",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Fable, one prompt: \"build an elaborate game that makes it feel like I'm a brilliant chess player without knowing anything at all about chess. It should make me feel like a grand master. Feel free to go as meta as you want but the more chess-y the better.\" https://t.co/XYVsgQpzPI https://t.co/ofRLmcf57j",
